  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp – these are your <strong>crispy potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1654618089478-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1654618089478-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1654618089478-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1654618089478-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1654618089478-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Soak the <strong>skewers</strong> in <strong>cold water</strong> (this prevents them from burning whilst cooking!)</p><p>Deseed the<strong> pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p><p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>coriander</strong> roughly, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1654618097974-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1654618097974-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1654618097974-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1654618097974-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1654618097974-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> pepper strips</strong>,<strong> sliced onion</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then cook for 2 min to soften slightly</p><p>Once softened, reduce the heat to low and cook for 10 min or until caramelised</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1654618104159-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1654618104159-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1654618104159-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1654618104159-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1654618104159-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>basa fillets</strong> into 4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[8]</span> strips, lengthways</p><p>Place the <strong>basa strips</strong> in a large mixing bowl with the <strong>smoked paprika</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>,<strong> </strong>then mix well to ensure the strips are coated</p><p>Thread each <strong>coated</strong> <strong>basa strip</strong> onto a <strong>soaked</strong> <strong>skewer</strong> in a snake-like fashion and set aside</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1654618108881-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1654618108881-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1654618108881-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1654618108881-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1654618108881-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once done, transfer the <strong>caramelised pepper & onion </strong>to a bowl (reserve the pan for later!)</p><p>Add<strong> half</strong> of the <strong>red wine vinegar </strong>(you’ll use the rest later!) to the bowl with 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Stir through the <strong>chopped coriander</strong> – this is your<strong> pepper & onion salsa</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1654618113245-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1654618113245-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1654618113245-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1654618113245-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1654618113245-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a high heat with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> coated basa skewers</strong> and cook for 3 min, turning once halfway, until browned on both sides</p><p>Once browned, reduce the heat to medium-high, cover with a lid and cook for a further 2 min or until cooked through – these are your <strong>smoky basa skewers</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1654618118376-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1654618118376-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1654618118376-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1654618118376-x1000.jpg",
